OL,6,FFreedom of Information requests
OL,7,Fsubmitted by ITV News to police forces
OL,8,Facross England and Wales reveal a
OL,9,Fsurge in vape spiking or poisoning
OL,10,Fincidents over the last five years.
OL,12,FChildren as young as 13 have had their
OL,13,Fvapes spiked with suspected class A
OL,14,Fand B drugs such as spice, fentanyl,
OL,15,Fcocaine, amphetamines and acid.
OL,17,FHundreds of incidents have occurred at
OL,18,Fschools, on trains and in hospitality
OL,19,Fvenues, most often with reusable vapes.
